  "response": "To start learning programming from scratch, here's a comprehensive roadmap:\n\n1. Choose a Beginner-Friendly Language\n- Python (Recommended for beginners)\n- JavaScript\n- Java\n- Ruby\n\n2. Learn Fundamentals\n- Basic syntax\n- Variables\n- Data types\n- Conditionals (if/else)\n- Loops\n- Functions\n- Basic data structures\n\n3. Free/Low-Cost Learning Resources\n- Online Platforms:\n  - Codecademy\n  - freeCodeCamp\n  - Coursera\n  - edX\n  - Khan Academy\n  - YouTube tutorials\n\n4. Practice Consistently\n- Code daily\n- Build small projects\n- Solve coding challenges\n- Use websites like:\n  - LeetCode\n  - HackerRank\n  - Project Euler\n\n5. Learn Programming Concepts\n- Object-Oriented Programming\n- Algorithm design\n- Data structures\n- Version control (Git)\n\n6. Build Projects\n- Personal websites\n- Simple games\n- Calculator\n- To-do list apps\n- Portfolio projects\n\n7. Additional Learning\n- Join coding communities\n- Attend workshops/meetups\n- Follow programming blogs\n- Watch coding YouTube channels\n\n8. Continuous Improvement\n- Learn new technologies\n- Stay updated with trends\n- Practice problem-solving\n\nRemember: Consistency and passion are key!",
